    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the culture, style, and period associated with the middle part of Ming dynasty, 1488-1505. The style is characterized by typically floral designs in white against a deep blue ground, in blue against a yellow ground, and in coffee brown against a white ground.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
